    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1867-01-26T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1867-01-26T00:00:00-05:00" n="239" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d239">
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Mr. Seward</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                                Campbell</persName>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 15.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <hi rend="italic">Washington,</hi>
                        </placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1867-01-26">
                            <hi rend="italic">January</hi> 26, 1867</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir:</hi> I send you herewith, for your information,
                            a memorandum<note n="*" xml:id="d239fn1">For this enclosure see
                                correspondence with the French legation. Page 290, vol. I.</note> of
                            a conversation which passed between me and Mr. Berthemy, the minister of
                            France to this country, on the 17th instant.</p>
                <p>I have also to inform you that our consul at Vera Cruz, Mr. Lane, has
                            resigned his position, and that upon his recommendation the name of Mr.
                            E. Saulnier, who has on various occasions acted as consul of the United
                            States to that city, has been sent to the Senate for confirmation in his
                            place.</p>
                <p>I am, sir, your obedient servant,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>WILLIAM H. SEWARD.</signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lewis D. Campbell</hi>, Esq., <hi rend="italic">&amp;c., &amp;c., &amp;c.</hi>
                    </p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
